               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Irshād al-ṭālibīn</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85093823 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_73-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21789">Irshād al-ṭālibīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21789">إرشاد الطالبين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on various aspects of occultism and Sufism, including quotations from the Qurʾān and Prophetic traditions, ascribed to <persName key="person_f7616" role="ant">Ṣūfī Khujandī </persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>The work consists of 4 rukn and a khātimah, but presently lacks an introduction and is defective at the beginning </p>
                        <p>Many careful annotations in margins </p>
                        <p>Loose slip between ff. 112-113 with Arabic aphorisms in praise of science and knowledge, with interlinear Urdu translation </p>
                        <p>Not dated </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian, Arabic &amp; Urdu </textLang>
                     <note>
